article.description: Dedrick Basile scored seven of his 21 points in a game-deciding 19-0 run in the second half as Cal State Bakersfield defeated Dartmouth 69-62 on Monday night.
article.headline: CS Bakersfield 69, Dartmouth 62
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Dedrick Basile scored a career-high 21 and Aly Ahmed had 16 points and a season-high 12 rebounds Monday night to lead Cal State Bakersfield past Dartmouth 69-62. Brent Wrapp, Kevin Mays and Jaylin Airington scored 10 apiece for Bakersfield (6-3). Mays had nine rebounds while Wrapp finished with seven assists. A 3-point play by Miles Wright put Dartmouth (3-5) up 33-32 early in the second half but the Big Green went scoreless for nearly seven minutes as the Roadrunners scored 19-straight points to make it 51-33 with 12:16 to play. Dartmouth responded with an 18-5 run that cut its deficit to five about eight minutes later, but the Big Green would get no closer. Evan Boudreaux made 1 of 2 free throws to make it 62-57 with 62 seconds left but Bakersfield made 5 of 6 free throws thereon to seal it. Boudreaux led Dartmouth with 14 points and eight rebounds.
